T1  - On quality bias and inflation targets
AU  - Schmitt-Grohé, Stephanie
AU  - Uribe, Martín
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 59
IS  - 4
SP  - 393
EP  - 400
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/05/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jmoneco.2012.02.002
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304393212000220
AB  - Does Ramsey optimal policy call for adjusting the inflation target by the size of the quality bias in measured inflation? We find that if it is nonhedonic (or sticker) prices that are sticky, the conventional view, according to which it is optimal to adjust the inflation target upward by the size of the quality bias, is misguided. Furthermore, we establish that quality improvement is crucial for the determination of the optimal inflation target even in the absence of quality bias. In this case, if nonhedonic prices are sticky, sticker prices should fall at the rate of quality growth.
